**Fixed the `browser4-cli` E2E HTTP request bug.** I hardened local Browser4 readiness in `sdks/browser4-cli/src/daemon.rs` so the CLI waits for both `/actuator/health` and MCP tool availability before treating a server as ready, made `kill_all_browsers()` wait for Chrome exits in `sdks/browser4-cli/src/managed_processes.rs`, and updated `sdks/browser4-cli/tests/e2e.rs` to match the current MCP `command_run` / `command_status` / `command_result` flow while widening retries for transient startup failures.

The original failure path now gets past `goto`: `test_e2e_interaction_console_and_export` and `test_e2e_agent_and_collective_commands` pass, and `test_e2e_mouse_and_dialog` no longer fails on the old `error sending request for url (.../mcp/call-tool)` bug. That mouse scenario still exposes a separate later `mousedown` issue, which I left isolated rather than folding into this fix. I also appended the required entries to `coworker\tasks\300logs\2026\04\13\MEMORY.20260413.md` and `coworker\tasks\300logs\2026\04\MEMORY.202604.md`.

